      • getFunctionalDatatypePropertyValue

        Literal getFunctionalDatatypePropertyValue(Resource subject,
                                           String propertyURI)
        Look up the value of a functional datatype property. Implementations should return null if there is no value for the property and should throw an error if there is more than one value.

      • getFunctionalObjectPropertyValue

        Resource getFunctionalObjectPropertyValue(Resource subject,
                                          String propertyURI)
        Look up the value of a functional object property. Implementations should return null if there is no value for the property and should throw an error if there is more than one value.

      • getInstances

        List<Resource> getInstances(String classURI)
        Look up all the instances of a class. Implementations should return an empty list if there are no instances, never null.

      • getObjectPropertyValues

        List<Resource> getObjectPropertyValues(Resource subject,
                                       String propertyURI)
        Look up the values of an object property. Implementations should never return null.
